Burischar Union () is a &lt;a href="Union%20Councils%20of%20Bangladesh"&gt;union&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href="Hathazari%20Upazila"&gt;Hathazari Upazila&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href="Chittagong%20District"&gt;Chittagong District&lt;/a&gt;.
Geography.
Area of Burischar: 946 acres (3.83 km2).
Location.
North: &lt;a href="Halda%20River"&gt;Halda River&lt;/a&gt;
East: &lt;a href="Chandgaon%20Thana"&gt;Chandgaon Thana&lt;/a&gt;
South: &lt;a href="Chandgaon%20Thana"&gt;Chandgaon Thana&lt;/a&gt;
West: &lt;a href="Shikarpur%20union"&gt;Shikarpur union&lt;/a&gt;
Population.
At the 1991 Bangladesh census, Burischar union had a population of 12,860 and 216 house units.
